headline: GCC Dark Chocolate Market Forecast and Company Analysis Report 2025-2033 Featuring Nestle, Hershey, Mondelez, Ferrero, Meiji, Bateel, Al-Seedawi Sweets, and AANI & DANI
summary: The GCC Dark Chocolate Market is poised for robust growth, expected to escalate from US$ 1.52 billion in 2024 to US$ 3.01 billion by 2033, with a CAGR of 7.90% from 2025 to 2033. Key drivers include heightened health awareness, increasing disposable incomes, and an expanding e-commerce sector. Dark chocolate's health benefits, such as antioxidant properties and reduced sugar content, fuel consumer demand. The market benefits from product innovation catering to diverse tastes and emerging trends
